cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with time synchronization and localization of IoT devices, which are typically connected through networks. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper evaluates the proposed algorithms on a quadrotor, which is a type of robot. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a framework for coordinating the actions of IoT devices, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed approach to solving the time synchronization and localization problems. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with coordinating the actions of multiple IoT devices, which can be seen as a multiagent system.
